August 19 at 3:28 PM ¬∑

BMS Safety & Informational Letter 2020-2021
Bayfield Middle School Students & Families - we're excited to see you soon!
If you haven't already read the BMS Safety & Informational Letter sent out by Principal Thurston on Monday, please see the link below.
https://documentcloud.adobe.com/link/review?uri=urn:aaid:scds:US:eaae5bc7-1b4e-4b18-b9c8-bb4eedc8139e

The letter reviews the various health precautions and new routines we're using at BMS this year to reduce the risk of COVID-19. Please discuss this with your family and let us know if you have any questions.
Wearing a mask to school is one of the new routines that might take some getting used to. Here are a couple fun photos to get you inspired!

Dear Bayfield Families,

Please visit our website for the attached final version 2.0 of the Opening of Schools Plan for 2020-2021. Please see page 2 for the executive summary of major changes from version 1.0. The new sport season calendars from the Colorado High School Activities Association is also included in the plan.

Thank you to those in our community who contributed 530 responses to our district survey that was utilized to update version 2.0.

Furthermore, we are thankful for the teams of teachers who met with the principal of each building to offer input and feedback into our final opening plan.

Warmly,

Dr. K. Kevin Aten
Superintendent of Schools
Bayfield School District

post_text:
2020-2021 School Year Budget Hearing

Tuesday, June 9, 2020
Notice of Public Budget Hearing for 2020-2021 School Year

BOARD OF EDUCATION
BAYFIELD SCHOOL DISTRICT 10 Jt-R

June 9, 2020

At the Work Session Meeting of the Board of Education on June 9, 2020, 6:00 p.m., the recording annual public budget hearing will take place. Public comment concerning the proposed budget will be permitted at this time.

Each speaker will give his/her full name, complete physical address, and then have a maximum of three minutes to speak to the board of education with topics related to the budget.

This meeting will be held electronically via Google Hangouts. Please email Brooke Laventure at blaventure@bayfield.k12.co.us if you would like to view or comment on the proposed budget.
This meeting will be recorded.

post_text:
You‚Äôre invited to a ribbon cutting ceremony for the PCC Southwest Bayfield Site on Tuesday, Sept. 24 at 4:30 pm at 658 E. South St. in Bayfield.

Explore our new college site offering classes and academic programs to both the community and concurrent enrollment students at Bayfield High School and our surrounding communities of Bayfield, Ignacio and Pagosa Springs. Learn how this collaborative campus shares resources and uses distance learning technology to maximize student success and competitive excellence.

ADA Notice: Reasonable accommodations will be provided upon request for persons with disabilities. To make a request, please notify the PCC Disability Resources Center at (719) 549-3446 or Disability Resources at least five working days before the event.

Join Annie Mombourquette from San Juan Basin Public Health and Madison LeBlanc from Fort Lewis College for an interactive workshop. As a result of this workshop, participants will be able to summarize trends, culture and health effects about youth use of electronic nicotine products and vaping and use trusted adult principles to have conversations with young people about these products.

The BHS Theatre program is happy to invite all students and teachers to our performance of ROALD DAHL‚ÄôS ‚ÄúMATILDA: THE MUSICAL!‚Äù

We have been working hard since December, and will present four performances in the Bayfield Performing Arts Center.

Friday March 15,

Saturday March 16,

Thursday March 21, and

Friday March 22.



All shows start at 7PM.
Tickets are $7 for students and seniors, and $10 for adults.

We are one of the first high schools to stage this new and exciting musical, and we hope you will be a part of it. We look forward to having you in our audience!

Sarah Ripley, Director and Derek Smith, Music Director

***Community Input Sought for New Strategic Plan***
Bayfield community residents, and stakeholders are invited to help shape the future of the school district by attending either strategic plan community input forum, at 6 p.m., Thursday, January 31, or 10:00 a.m., Saturday, February 2, at Bayfield High School Library/Media Center, 800 CR 501, in Bayfield.

post_text: We realize that the current Federal government shutdown may be creating some financial hardship for families in our community. We welcome these families to submit a free and reduced meal application that reflects any reduction in family income. Please visit our website to access a meal application. We will process these applications immediately and award free or reduced meal benefits to your family accordingly.

post_text:
BIS NEWS
School Safety
School staff across the district have recently been made aware of a problem involving underage
vaping of nicotine-related products at schools and on district transportation. It is important that
our students and parents understand that there are stiff penalties for using or possessing these
items at school. Please refer to the attached document to learn more about this trend.

School Safety
School staff across the district have recently been made aware of a problem involving underage
vaping of nicotine-related products at schools and on district transportation. It is important that
our students and parents understand that there are stiff penalties for using or possessing these

post_text:
School has been cancelled at the Primary School today. Please make plans to pick up your child as soon as possible at Bayfield Intermediate School, 720 East Oak Drive. You will be required to check in at the main office for safety and verification reasons. No leak has been found however, it will take another two to three hours before a definitive decision can be made. Please do not call the primary school. There is no staff to receive your call.

As a result Bayfield Family Center will be closed today also.

post_text:
Dear Bayfield School District,

Please join family and friends of Troy Zabel for a Celebration of Life to honor his numerous personal and the professional contributions on Saturday, October 13, 2018, at 1 P.M. at Bayfield High School Performing Arts Center, 800 County Road 501, Bayfield, CO 81122 (doors open at 12:30 P.M.). Immediately following, at approximately 2 P.M., family and friends are then invited to join us for food, stories, laughs, and, of course, a toast to Troy at Eagle Park, on the south side of Bayfield Town Hall at 1169 Highway 160 B, Bayfield, CO.

Sincerely,

‚Äîkevin

Dr. K. Kevin Aten
Superintendent of Schools
Bayfield School District
Together, we are: "Your Learning Place"
katen@bayfield.k12.co.us
